cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI

The paper discusses a problem related to game theory and social interactions, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) categories. The problem involves finding the maximum independent cut in a graph, which is a graph theory problem, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and its approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
